Get the posterior of the probabilities

Source: R/bpc_get_probabilities.R
get_probabilities_posterior.Rd

Get the posterior of the probabilities

get_probabilities_posterior(bpc_object, newdata = NULL, n = 1000)

Arguments

bpc_object

a bpc object
newdata

default to NULL. If used, it will calculate the probabilities only for the newdata. Otherwise it will calculate for all combinations
n

number of samples to draw from the posterior

Value

a matrix with the corresponding posterior

Examples

# \donttest{
m<-bpc(data = tennis_agresti,
player0 = 'player0',
player1 = 'player1',
result_column = 'y',
model_type = 'bt',
solve_ties = 'none')
